[SN]TITLE[SN]
Light aircraft pilot tried to avoid Nottinghamshire council van

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A pilot whose light aircraft hit a moving van during takeoff had attempted to manoeuvre around the vehicle, an air accident report says.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Socata TB9 "clipped" a Nottinghamshire County Council van which was driving along a road at the end of Lambley Airstrip on 24 March.
The Air Accidents Investigation Branch (AAIB) report said the 69-year-old pilot tried to climb the plane when he spotted the van during takeoff.
The driver and pilot were uninjured.
